This is a list of episodes of the 15th season of Power Rangers, [[Power Rangers
Operation Overdrive]].

{{Episode list/sublist|List of Power Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=605 |EpisodeNumber2=1 |Title=Kick Into Overdrive
 I |DirectedBy = |WrittenBy = |OriginalAirDate= |ShortSummary= Explorer Andrew
 Hartford finds the crown of the Corona Aurora, an extremely powerful artifact
 which, when reunited with its five missing jewels, could be used for good or
 evil. However when he inadvertently awakens Moltor and Flurious who also seek
 the jewels of the crown, he recruits four talented citizens to become Power
 Rangers and plans to become the Red Ranger. However when the evil forces
 attack, it is soon left to Andrew's son Mack to take action. }} {{Episode
 list/sublist|List of Power Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=606 |EpisodeNumber2=2 |Title=Kick Into Overdrive
 II |DirectedBy = |WrittenBy = |OriginalAirDate= |ShortSummary= Mack wishes to
 continue as the Red Ranger, however he is opposed by Mr. Hartford who doesn't
 wish for his son to get involved. However the situation worsens when Moltor
 steals the Crown and kidnaps Mr. Hartford, resulting in Mack leading a rescue
 attempt. }} {{Episode list/sublist|List of Power Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=607 |EpisodeNumber2=3 |Title=The Underwater World
 |DirectedBy = Mark Beesley |WrittenBy = John Tellegen |OriginalAirDate=
 |ShortSummary= The search for the first jewel of the Corona Aurora begins when
 Andrew discovers Atlantis. Believing the first jewel to be hidden there, the
 Rangers travel to the undersea continent however problems arise when Will
 refuses to cooperate with the rest of the team. }} {{Episode list/sublist|List
 of Power Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=608 |EpisodeNumber2=4 |Title=Heart of Blue
 |DirectedBy = Britta Johnstone |WrittenBy = David Garber |OriginalAirDate=
 |ShortSummary= With the scroll from Atlantis, the Rangers need to find the
 other two in order to continue with the jewel quest. Meanwhile Dax falls in
 love with a girl named Mira, but seeing her is interfering with his job.
 However things soon become far worse when it is revealed that Mira is actually
 Miratrix, another villain who is also seeking the scrolls. }} {{Episode
 list/sublist|List of Power Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=609 |EpisodeNumber2=5 |Title=Weather or Not
 |DirectedBy = Britta Johnstone |WrittenBy = John Tellegen |OriginalAirDate=
 |ShortSummary= As the Rangers prepare to head to St. Lucia to search for the
 first jewel Moltor steals a weather machine and prepares to destroy Earth with
 it. Mack questions his status as the Red Ranger when he puts a bystander in
 jeopardy. However when the Weather Machine manages to defeat the Zords and
 traps the other Rangers in a chasm, Mack must put his doubts to the side if he
 is to successfully pilot the newest Zord, the Drill Driver. }} {{Episode
 list/sublist|List of Power Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=610 |EpisodeNumber2=6 |Title=Pirate in Pink
 |DirectedBy = Britta Johnstone |WrittenBy = Jackie Marchand |OriginalAirDate=
 |ShortSummary=The Rangers begin the final leg of the first jewel quest on St.
 Lucia, however while the other Rangers worry about running into the ghost of
 Brownbeard the Pirate, Rose refuses to believe in the supernatural spirit.
 However the ghost of Brownbeard does turn up also searching for the jewel, Rose
 finds herself forced to trust him while trying to keep it away from Miratrix.
 }} {{Episode list/sublist|List of Power Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=611 |EpisodeNumber2=7 |Title=At All Costs
 |DirectedBy = Jonathan Brough |WrittenBy = Bruce Kalish |OriginalAirDate=
 |ShortSummary= With Brownbeard's pearl safely in the Rangers' hands, the gang
 have some time-off however their fun and games are made sour due to Ronny's
 desire to beat the others no matter what they're competing in. Moltor meanwhile
 turns one of his Lava Lizards into Volkan and attempts to get a Dragon Scale to
 make him more powerful while the Rangers try to find the same scale that will
 allow them to wield the new Defender Vest and the overpowerful Drill Blaster.
 }} {{Episode list/sublist|List of Power Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=612 |EpisodeNumber2=8 |Title=Both Sides Now
 |DirectedBy = Jonathan Brough |WrittenBy = David Garber |OriginalAirDate=
 |ShortSummary=The gang's search for the Hou-ou bird leads to a dead end,
 however they have more important things to worry about when Will is suddenly
 "fired" by Andrew and "sides" with Miratrix. While the other Rangers scramble
 to find him, Will assists Miratrix in releasing Kamdor, her Ninja Master. }}
 {{Episode list/sublist|List of Power Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=613 |EpisodeNumber2=9 |Title=Follow The Ranger
 |DirectedBy = Jonathan Brough |WrittenBy = John Tellegen |OriginalAirDate=
 |ShortSummary=Mack misinterprets Andrew's concern over his status as a Ranger
 as a lack of confidence. Meanwhile, Moltor and Flurious team up to steal the
 DriveMax Megazord, capturing Mack in the process. While the other Rangers try
 to locate their leader and the Megazord, Mack finds that the key to his escape
 may be the rivalry between his two captors... with a little assistance from
 Norg. }} {{Episode list/sublist|List of Power Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=614 |EpisodeNumber2=10 |Title=Lights, Camera, DAX
 |DirectedBy = Mike Smith |WrittenBy = John Tellegen |OriginalAirDate=
 |ShortSummary= Miratrix and Kamdor are looking for the Toru Diamond using the
 parchment left behind by the Hou-ou bird. Moltor interferes with their search
 and uses a monster against the two. Meanwhile, Dax wants to try out for a role
 in a movie, and when Andrew tells him no, he is forced to make a decision
 between his lifelong dream and his responsibilities as a Ranger. }} {{Episode
 list/sublist|List of Power Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=615 |EpisodeNumber2=11 |Title=Face to Face I
 |DirectedBy = Mike Smith |WrittenBy = Jackie Marchand |OriginalAirDate=
 |ShortSummary= The Rangers try to translate the parchment that was recovered
 from Miratrix and Kamdor, but are ambushed by monsters sent by Moltor. Mack
 discovers that one of the monsters, an alien named Tyzonn, may not be evil, and
 tries to figure out the truth behind his actions. }} {{Episode
 list/sublist|List of Power Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=616 |EpisodeNumber2=12 |Title=Face to Face II
 |DirectedBy = Mike Smith |WrittenBy = Jackie Marchand |OriginalAirDate=
 |ShortSummary= Mack and Tyzonn are ambushed by Bullox and a group of Lava
 Lizards as the other Rangers try to find Mack and claim the next jewel of the
 crown. }} {{Episode list/sublist|List of Power Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=617 |EpisodeNumber2=13 |Title=Man of Mercury I
 |DirectedBy = |WrittenBy = |OriginalAirDate= |ShortSummary= When an expedition
 camp in Brazil find the first clue towards finding the third jewel of the
 Corona Aurora, they are attacked by new villains known as the Fearcats. The
 Rangers attempt to stop them only to find their paths crossing with Tyzonn
 again. }} {{Episode list/sublist|List of Power Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=618 |EpisodeNumber2=14 |Title=Man of Mercury II
 |DirectedBy = Charlie Haskell |WrittenBy = John Tellegen |OriginalAirDate=
 |ShortSummary= Flurious tests his gyros on the Fearcats, Mig and Benglo,
 turning them into powerful cyborgs. It is a race against time for the Rangers
 to save Tyzonn and stop the Fearcats from destroying San Angeles. }} {{Episode
 list/sublist|List of Power Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=619 |EpisodeNumber2=15 |Title=Behind the Scenes
 |DirectedBy = Charlie Haskell |WrittenBy = Jackie Marchand |OriginalAirDate=
 |ShortSummary= The Rangers are invited to perform an on-air interview for a
 popular talk show. Flurious, Kamdor, Miratrix, and the Fearcats join in an
 extremely shaky alliance and while Kamdor and Miratrix target Tyzonn, the
 others start to hit the Rangers with several sequential attacks. With their
 zords are taken out by Flurious's robot, the Rangers must rely on Tyzonn and
 his new zords to save the day. }} {{Episode list/sublist|List of Power
 Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=620 |EpisodeNumber2=16 |Title=Just Like Me
 |DirectedBy = |WrittenBy = |OriginalAirDate= |ShortSummary= The Rangers travel
 to Norway and race Moltor to the mystical hammer Mjolnir. Moltor retrieves it
 first, and the adventure is compounded by Tyzonn's sudden desire to emulate
 Will, and Will's annoyance at this. Tyzonn is forced to learn the benefits of
 being himself as they attempt to take Mjolnir back. }} {{Episode
 list/sublist|List of Power Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=621 |EpisodeNumber2=17 |Title=It's Hammer Time
 |DirectedBy = Vanessa Alexander |WrittenBy = John Tellegen |OriginalAirDate=
 |ShortSummary= Tracing the connection between the Cannon of Ki Amuk and
 Mjolnir, the Rangers travel to Mexico and are ambushed. In the process, Loki
 appears, masquerading as Thor, and steals Mjolnir. To get it back, Spencer
 disguises himself as the goddess Freyja. }} {{Episode list/sublist|List of
 Power Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=622 |EpisodeNumber2=18 |Title=Out of Luck
 |DirectedBy = Vanessa Alexander |WrittenBy = |OriginalAirDate= |ShortSummary=
 After the Rangers use the Cannon of Ki Amuk and Mjolnir to get the Piedra Aztec
 del CompÃ¡s it gets stolen by Moltor. Moltor sends Blothgaar to fight the
 Rangers. Mack is blasted by the compass and is overcome by a serious case of a
 bad luck. The rangers gave him their good luck charms. }} {{Episode
 list/sublist|List of Power Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=623 |EpisodeNumber2=19 |Title=One Gets Away
 |DirectedBy = Vanessa Alexander |WrittenBy = |OriginalAirDate= |ShortSummary=
 Using the compass, the Rangers finally find the Blue Sapphire which is third
 jewel of the Corona Aurora. Will is entrusted to get it back to the base, but
 is ambushed by Kamdor and Miratrix, and loses it to the villainous pair. With
 Andrew angered at him, he resigns, only to have Spencer offer him another
 chance. Meanwhile, Moltor offers the Fearcats some invincible Super Armor. With
 their latest Giant Robot already giving the Rangers a tough time, can Will get
 to the Armor before the Fearcats, and make up for his prior failure? }}
 {{Episode list/sublist|List of Power Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=624 |EpisodeNumber2=20 |Title=Once a Ranger I
 |DirectedBy = Britta Johnstone |WrittenBy = Jackie Marchand |OriginalAirDate=
 |ShortSummary= The son of Lord Zedd and Rita Repulsa, Thrax, unites all four
 Corona Aurora-seeking factions of villains into a new Evil Alliance. When they
 manage to overwhelm the Overdrive Rangers, their connection to the Morphing
 Grid is severed, and their powers destroyed! With the gems still needing
 protecting, Sentinel Knight assembles a team of replacement Rangers, made up of
 members of previous (or future) teams of Power Rangers. Will they be enough to
 stop the Evil Alliance? And will the former Overdrive Rangers be able to assist
 with just their genetically enhanced abilities? }} {{Episode list/sublist|List
 of Power Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=625 |EpisodeNumber2=21 |Title=Once a Ranger II
 |DirectedBy = Britta Johnstone |WrittenBy = Jackie Marchand |OriginalAirDate=
 |ShortSummary= No longer having Ranger powers, the former Overdrive Rangers
 return to their civilian lives. All but Mack, who learns of Thrax's plans to
 destroy the Sentinel Knight, and seeks out the only item capable of doing so,
 the legendary sword Excelsior. Will he be doing this alone, or can the call of
 action prove the adage of "Once a Ranger, Always a Ranger" to his former
 teammates? Meanwhile, their replacements, the team of Returning Rangers, head
 to Angel Grove to seek out the only being capable of repairing the Morphing
 Grid: Alpha 6! Even if they succeed, can two combined teams of Power Rangers
 stop Thrax for good, and permanently break up the Evil Alliance? }} {{Episode
 list/sublist|List of Power Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=626 |EpisodeNumber2=22 |Title=One Fine Day
 |DirectedBy = Britta Johnstone |WrittenBy = Bruce Kalish |OriginalAirDate=
 |ShortSummary= The Rangers get a day off, and plan a relaxing picnic in the
 forest. Unfortunately for Rose, Tyzonn is obsessed with getting to know her
 better, which goes from flattery to annoyance very quickly. The Fearcats just
 happen to be in the same forest, and while searching for the powerful Centurion
 Torch to use in their latest Giant Robot, they put up a Lamporean force field.
 Our heroes bump into it, and despite Tyzonn claiming that forming a human chain
 with his Mercurian powers will allow them passage, they end up separated...
 with Rose stuck inside the force field with Tyzonn!}} {{Episode
 list/sublist|List of Power Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=627 |EpisodeNumber2=23 |Title=Ronny on Empty I
 |DirectedBy = Mike Smith |WrittenBy = John Tellegen |OriginalAirDate=
 |ShortSummary= Ronny is kidnapped by the Fearcats, while Will disobeys orders
 to go after her. Meanwhile, a clue from the Centurion Torch leads the other
 Rangers to Egypt. }} {{Episode list/sublist|List of Power Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=628 |EpisodeNumber2=24 |Title=Ronny on Empty II
 |DirectedBy = Mike Smith |WrittenBy = John Tellegen |OriginalAirDate=
 |ShortSummary= Will saves Ronny from having her energy drained, and the Rangers
 battle Moltor's new robot with a new Megazord. }} {{Episode list/sublist|List
 of Power Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=629 |EpisodeNumber2=25 |Title=Things Not Said
 |DirectedBy = Mike Smith |WrittenBy = David Garber |OriginalAirDate=
 |ShortSummary= The Rangers battle one of Kamdor's monsters that gives their
 system a virus. Mack is revealed to be an android made by Andrew Hartford.
 Mack then becomes enraged at his father, Andrew convinces Mack to help the
 other Rangers. Mack then says he'll go but he's taking Rose's new robot
 technology, he arrives at the fight and activates the Sentinel Sword getting
 his battilizer and becoming the Red Sentinel Ranger, defeating all of Kamdor's
 monsters. Kamdor flees with the Star of Isis but at the last second Ronny uses
 her super speed to steal the jewel. }} {{Episode list/sublist|List of Power
 Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=630 |EpisodeNumber2=26 |Title=Red Ranger
 Unplugged |DirectedBy = Jonathan Brough |WrittenBy = John Tellegen
 |OriginalAirDate= |ShortSummary= Mack tries to find a new identity for himself
 and takes up the guitar. Also, the Rangers battle a new Fearcat, Crazar, while
 Mig and Benglo look for the Octavian Chalice. }} {{Episode list/sublist|List of
 Power Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=631 |EpisodeNumber2=27 |Title=Home and Away I
 |DirectedBy = Jonathan Brough |WrittenBy = Jackie Marchand |OriginalAirDate=
 |ShortSummary=Mig and Benglo access the power of the Octavian Chalice and
 create Agrios, which takes severely damages the Megazords. Meanwhile, after a
 battle with Kamdor and Miratrix, Tyzonn is knocked unconscious and awakes on
 his home planet with his fiance. }} {{Episode list/sublist|List of Power
 Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=632 |EpisodeNumber2=28 |Title=Home and Away II
 |DirectedBy = Jonathan Brough |WrittenBy = Jackie Marchand |OriginalAirDate=
 |ShortSummary=Tyzonn begins to have doubts regarding his reunion with his old
 fiance. Meanwhile, Mack attacks the Fearcats in the Flash Point Megazord
 willing to sacrifice himself to stop Agrios. The Rangers eventually defeat
 Agrios, The Fearcats try to escape with the Octavian Chalice but the Rangers
 show up ready to finish the battle once and for all. }} {{Episode
 list/sublist|List of Power Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=633 |EpisodeNumber2=29 |Title=Way Back When
 |DirectedBy = Jonathan Brough |WrittenBy = John Tellegen |OriginalAirDate=
 |ShortSummary=The Rangers view Mack's memories on a video screen to remind
 themselves of the status of each jewel, to figure out who has them, and to try
 to figure out where to begin their search for the final jewel. They first view
 the locations of the four earlier jewels, which proves fruitless, but thanks to
 a little help from Spencer, they eventually reveal the next location: Greece.
 }} {{Episode list/sublist|List of Power Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=634 |EpisodeNumber2=30 |Title=Two Fallen Foes
 |DirectedBy = Mark Beesley |WrittenBy = John Tellegen |OriginalAirDate=
 |ShortSummary= The Rangers travel to Greece, where they invoke an ancient
 ritual in order to find the next jewel. Kamdor, angry that Miratrix failed him
 again, berates her. Miratrix, seeking more power, intercepts the ritual and
 becomes a giant bird-like creature. After being defeated by the Battlefleet
 Megazord, Kamdor then imprisons her inside the crystal where he was
 imprisoned. He now makes his final act: summoning a meteor with the power of
 the Blue Sapphire, and challenges the Rangers. While the rest battle the
 meteor, Will battles Kamdor. In the end, Will defeats Kamdor, and the Rangers
 destroy the meteor. They then travel to Egypt, and now need a key to open the
 Sarcophagus, with Moltor on the trail. }} {{Episode list/sublist|List of Power
 Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=635 |EpisodeNumber2=31 |Title=Nothing to Lose
 |DirectedBy = Mark Beesley |WrittenBy = Jackie Marchand |OriginalAirDate=
 |ShortSummary=With the Blue Sapphire now in his possession, Flurious uses its
 power to start destroying Moltor's volcano. Meanwhile the Rangers head to
 Japan to find the Tri-Dragon key which is needed to open the Tomb which they
 hope contains the next jewel. Mack, having decided he is the most expendable
 member to the team due to his android nature, starts to place himself in more
 and more dangerous situations and this comes to a head when he decides to go
 to Moltor's volcano to retrieve the crown. Although he is unsuccessful, Moltor
 is severely weakened and travels to Flurious' ice lair with the crown. However
 with both the crown and one of the jewels in his possession, Flurious quickly
 disposes of his brother and plans to take care of the Rangers next. Meanwhile
 the Rangers learn that the fifth jewel of the Corona may have been far closer
 than they could ever have imagined... }} {{Episode list/sublist|List of Power
 Rangers episodes
 |- LineColor= BCC9D2
 |ImageCaption= |EpisodeNumber=636 |EpisodeNumber2=32 |Title=Crown and
 Punishment |DirectedBy = Mark Beesley |WrittenBy = Bruce Kalish
 |OriginalAirDate= |ShortSummary=The Rangers retrieve the fifth jewel however
 are immediately ambushed by Flurious, the only villain left and he manages to
 take the four jewels that the Rangers possess. Now with all five jewels and the
 crown, Flurious plans to reassemble the Corona Aurora and unleash his wrath
 upon the world....
----
Note: This episode aired in the United Kingdom on , before the United States'
      broadcast. }}
|}
